Finally saw Backrooms last night. Whoa. Starts normal but descends into this crazy metaphysical horror. Has elements of The Shining and the video for Tom Petty's Don't Come Around Here No More. Really, really good movie (minus the very end). Actors were great. Set in 1990 and they nailed the feel of that era. Both my kid and I gave it 9/10. We also saw Obsession month ago and gave that 7/10 so this was bit better.

Also this is so specific but for any Radiohead nerds out there you'll get it: I kept thinking how the movie, and the concept of being trapped in your subconscious, had the same vibe as Kid A / Amnesiac (esp the weirder songs like Push/Pulk Revolving Doors). Anyhow, the guy who made this movie i hope he does more

@AmadeusVidet I coukd see it not appealing to everyone, it’s weird,  but I just felt wonderfully lost in this other world.

@DaveNadig I know you and you will dig it. Hard to believe they even gave money to make something this ambitiously weird. Good sign.

@intellivisi0x Haha perfect my wife has said similar to me

